From a94a742cc9fe5a907be3ad970646abe1b8e39f80 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jan200101 <sentrycraft123@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 19:10:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add Vulkan discrete detection

This implementation differs a little from the others, there is no way
to get a Vulkan device from a DRM handle so instead we make use of
the VK_EXT_physical_device_drm extension and find which Vulkan device
matches our major and minor number, any matching devices will then have
its VkPhysicalDeviceType checked to see if it is discrete or not.

Signed-off-by: Jan200101 <sentrycraft123@gmail.com>
---
 .gitlab-ci.yml                         |   1 +
 data/30-discrete-gpu.rules.in          |   4 +
 meson.build                            |   1 +
 meson_options.txt                      |   6 +
 src/discrete-detection/meson.build     |  11 ++
 src/discrete-detection/vulkan.c        | 166 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 tests/discrete-detection/meson.build   |  47 +++++++
 tests/discrete-detection/vulkan_mock.c | 147 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 8 files changed, 383 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 src/discrete-detection/vulkan.c
 create mode 100644 tests/discrete-detection/vulkan_mock.c

